================================================================================
Why this license (rationale)
================================================================================

Plane Old Weather is SOURCE-AVAILABLE, not open source. The intent is: anyone
may read, fork, modify, and run this project locally — for personal,
educational, evaluation, and reference purposes — but PUBLIC DEPLOYMENT (hosting
or serving the project, or any derivative of it, on a public network or external
domain) is reserved to Bow Echo LLC and requires prior written permission.

Three license options were evaluated against that intent:

  • Business Source License 1.1 (BUSL-1.1) — A source-available license, but it
    REQUIRES a "Change Date" no more than four years after publication, on which
    the work AUTOMATICALLY converts to a GPL-compatible open-source license. That
    mandatory, time-limited conversion is incompatible with a perpetual
    restriction on public deployment, and BUSL frames its restriction around
    "production use" rather than deployment specifically. Rejected.

  • CC-BY-NC-4.0 — A Creative Commons content license. Its NonCommercial term
    forbids commercial use but does NOT restrict non-commercial public
    deployment, so on its own it would not stop someone from re-hosting the site
    non-commercially. Creative Commons also advises against applying CC licenses
    to source code. It is, however, the right fit for prose and figures, and is
    used for them in Section 2. Rejected for the code.

  • A custom source-available license — Expresses the intent most precisely and
    enforceably: a narrow grant for local and private use, plus an explicit,
    unambiguous prohibition on public deployment without written permission, with
    all other rights reserved under copyright. Chosen for the code.

Accordingly, this LICENSE applies a custom source-available license to the
software (Section 1) and CC-BY-NC-4.0 to the written content and figures
(Section 2).

